      "nodeType": "heading-2",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "How often should you get a roof inspection?",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Most homeowners should ",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "schedule professional roof inspections twice per year",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": " - once in the spring and once in the fall. These seasonal checks help identify any damage from winter storms or summer weather before small issues become major problems.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "blockquote",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "paragraph",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "I've found that even on roofs that look perfectly fine from the ground, ",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "a closer look often reveals minor uplifted shingles",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": " or blockages in valleys you’d never spot otherwise.",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "You'll need additional inspections after severe weather events like hailstorms, severe gales, or flash floods. If you live in an area prone to extreme weather, consider quarterly inspections.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "For newer roofs under 5 years old, annual inspections may suffice if there haven't been any significant weather events. Don't wait for obvious signs of damage to call an inspector. Regular inspections can catch problems early, extend your roof's lifespan, and protect your warranty coverage. They're also essential when you're planning to buy or sell a home.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "heading-3",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Drone Roof Inspection Frequency by Building Type",
