          "value": "Should you get a roof inspection after severe weather or storms?",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Beyond regular maintenance schedules, ",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "hyperlink",
          "data": {
            "uri": "/blog/storm-damage-roof-inspections"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "severe weather events",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": " demand immediate attention to your roof's condition. ",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "You should schedule an inspection after any major storm",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": " involving hail, high winds, heavy snow, or flying debris. These elements can cause hidden damage that might lead to leaks and structural issues if left unchecked.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Don't wait for visible signs of damage to appear inside your home. By then, the problem may have already escalated.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "A prompt inspection after severe weather can identify issues like lifted shingles, damaged flashing, or compromised seals around vents and chimneys.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "blockquote",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "paragraph",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "My advice is to not underestimate high winds. I often spot subtle but significant ",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "'creasing'",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": " on asphalt shingles where the wind has lifted and folded them back. ",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "It’s a classic entry point for water",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": " that you’re unlikely to see without a detailed, close-up look.",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "If you've experienced multiple storms in succession, it's even more critical to have a professional assess your roof's integrity. Quick action can prevent minor storm damage from becoming a major repair expense.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "heading-2",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "When is the best time of year to schedule a roof inspection?",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Timing your annual roof inspection strategically can maximize its effectiveness and value. ",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "The best time to schedule an inspection is during early fall",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": ", before winter weather sets in. This allows you to identify and fix any issues before snow, ice, and freezing temperatures can worsen existing damage.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Spring serves as your second-best option. After winter's harsh conditions, you'll want to check for any damage caused by ice dams, heavy snow loads, or freeze-thaw cycles. However, you may face longer wait times during spring as many homeowners discover winter damage.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "blockquote",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "paragraph",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "From a practical standpoint, I also find ",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": "the light in spring and fall is much better for spotting subtle issues",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ],
              "data": {}
            },
            {
              "nodeType": "text",
              "value": " like dents from hail or granule loss, compared to the harsh glare of a summer afternoon.",
              "marks": [],
              "data": {}
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Avoid scheduling inspections during summer's intense heat or winter's severe weather. These conditions can make it dangerous for inspectors to work on your roof and may prevent them from spotting certain problems effectively.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
