    {
      "nodeType": "heading-2",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "What happens if you skip regular roof inspections?",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Skipping regular roof inspections can lead to severe and costly consequences for your home. Without professional assessments, small issues like loose shingles or minor leaks can quickly escalate into major structural damage.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Water infiltration may cause rotting wood, mould growth, and compromised insulation before you notice any visible signs inside your house. You'll likely miss early warning signs that could have been addressed with simple repairs.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "This can lead to extensive damage that requires complete roof replacement. Additionally, ",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "neglecting inspections often voids your roof warranty",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "data": {}
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": " and can result in insurance claim denials if problems arise. The money you think you're saving by avoiding routine inspections will be far outweighed by the thousands you'll spend fixing preventable damage.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "heading-2",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "How routine inspections extend the lifespan of your roof",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Regular roof inspections can dramatically boost your roof's longevity. They work by catching and fixing minor problems before they turn into major issues. During these inspections, professionals can spot early signs of wear, loose shingles, or small leaks that you might miss.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "By addressing problems early, you'll prevent water damage to your roof's structural components and avoid costly repairs down the line.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "Professional inspectors can identify and seal entry points where moisture might penetrate, replace damaged flashing, and ensure proper ventilation. These are all factors that contribute to a longer-lasting roof. Your roof can last several years beyond its expected lifespan when you maintain a consistent inspection schedule.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
