    {
      "nodeType": "heading-2",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "What are the warning signs you need a roof inspection sooner?",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "paragraph",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "text",
          "value": "While routine inspections are essential, certain warning signs demand immediate professional attention for your roof.",
          "marks": [],
          "data": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "nodeType": "unordered-list",
      "data": {},
      "content": [
        {
          "nodeType": "list-item",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "paragraph",
              "data": {},
              "content": [
                {
                  "nodeType": "text",
                  "value": "If you notice water stains on your ceiling, peeling paint, or damp spots in your attic, you're likely dealing with a leak that needs quick assessment.",
                  "marks": [],
                  "data": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "list-item",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "paragraph",
              "data": {},
              "content": [
                {
                  "nodeType": "text",
                  "value": "Missing, cracked, or curled shingles are red flags that your roof's protective layer is compromised.",
                  "marks": [],
                  "data": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "list-item",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "paragraph",
              "data": {},
              "content": [
                {
                  "nodeType": "text",
                  "value": "Watch for excessive granules in your gutters, as this indicates shingle deterioration.",
                  "marks": [],
                  "data": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "list-item",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "paragraph",
              "data": {},
              "content": [
                {
                  "nodeType": "text",
                  "value": "You should also check for sagging areas, which could signal structural issues.",
                  "marks": [],
                  "data": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "list-item",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "paragraph",
              "data": {},
              "content": [
                {
                  "nodeType": "text",
                  "value": "After severe weather events like hailstorms or high winds, inspect for visible damage.",
                  "marks": [],
                  "data": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "nodeType": "list-item",
          "data": {},
          "content": [
            {
              "nodeType": "paragraph",
              "data": {},
              "content": [
                {
                  "nodeType": "text",
                  "value": "If you spot daylight coming through your roof boards or feel drafts in your attic, don't wait for your next scheduled inspection - call a professional immediately.",
                  "marks": [],
                  "data": {}
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
